<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B76164778E8FB70264FF9F1" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B76164778E8FB702494FA28" blockId="6.[136,1452,1022,2057]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B76164778E8FB702699FB65" bold="true" box="[189,451,1202,1228]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Nomenclatural notes:</emphasis>
— 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B76164779B5FB702581FB65" author="Brandao, J. L. &amp; Baracho, G. S. &amp; De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V." box="[480,731,1202,1228]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="205 - 227" refId="ref18144" refString="Brandao, J. L., Baracho, G. S., De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V. (2017) Synopsis of Sida (Malvaceae, Malvoideae, Malveae) in the state of Pernambuco, Brazil. Phytotaxa 307 (3): 205 - 227. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 307.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477A1CFB7125DFFB65" box="[585,645,1202,1228]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
(2017)
</bibRefCitation>
presented the type of the species as a 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7616477CFEFB70224AFB65" box="[1195,1296,1202,1228]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">holotype</typeStatus>
, deposited in herbarium P. However, there are several specimens from the collection 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477BEBFB14233EFB59" box="[958,1124,1238,1264]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
Hassler 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7616477C4BFB14233EFB59" box="[1054,1124,1238,1264]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.680208" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" unit="in" value="10552.0">10552</quantity>
</emphasis>
in other herbaria, and so all specimens are 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7616477963FB3926C6FABC" box="[310,412,1275,1301]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">syntypes</typeStatus>
. According to the International Code of Nomenclature of algae, fungi and plants, 2018, from 
<date id="7358104D0B7616477893FADD2626FA91" box="[198,380,1310,1337]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" value="2001-01-01">January 1, 2001</date>
, a lectotypification will only be effective when accompanied by the term “ 
<typeStatus id="D85D882F0B7616477C90FADC2264FA91" box="[1221,1342,1310,1336]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">lectotypus</typeStatus>
” or by its abbreviation or its equivalent in a modern language (Art. 9.23, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477B0EFA802360FAF5" author="Turland, N. J. &amp; Wiersema, J. H. &amp; Barrie, F. R. &amp; Greuter, W. &amp; Hawksworth, D. L. &amp; Herendeen, P. S. &amp; Knapp, S. &amp; Kusber, W. - H. &amp; Li, D. - Z. &amp; Marhold, K. &amp; May, T. W. &amp; McNeill, J. &amp; Monro, A. M. &amp; Prado, J. &amp; Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F." box="[859,1082,1346,1373]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref20537" refString="Turland, N. J., Wiersema, J. H., Barrie, F. R., Greuter, W., Hawksworth, D. L., Herendeen, P. S., Knapp, S., Kusber, W. - H., Li, D. - Z., Marhold, K., May, T. W., McNeill, J., Monro, A. M., Prado, J., Price, M. J. &amp; Smith, G. F. (Eds.) (2018) International Code of Nomenclature for algae, fungi, and plants (Shenzhen Code) adopted by the Nineteenth International Botanical Congress Shenzhen, China, July 2017. Regnum Vegetabile 159. Koeltz Botanical Books, Glashutten, 304 pp. https: // doi. org / 10.12705 / Code. 2018" type="book" year="2018">
Turland 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477BEEFA8124B4FAF5" box="[955,1006,1346,1372]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), and when including the phrase “designated here” (Art. 7.11). Therefore, a lectotypification was necessary.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="0759368D0B76164778E8FA48264FF9F1" blockId="6.[136,1452,1022,2057]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B76164778E8FA4826D4FA0D" bold="true" box="[189,398,1418,1444]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Taxonomic notes:</emphasis>
—The species belongs to Sect. 
<taxonomicName id="C0E64D0E0B7616477ABEFA482431FA0D" authorityName="Fryxell" authorityYear="1985" baseAuthorityName="de Candolle" box="[747,875,1418,1444]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Caryophyllaceae" genus="Cordifoliae" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" order="Caryophyllales" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477ABEFA482431FA0D" box="[747,875,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Cordifoliae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477B2DFA482332FA0D" author="Monteiro-Filho, H. C." box="[888,1128,1418,1444]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref19920" refString="Monteiro-Filho, H. C. (1936) Monografia da Malvaceae Brasileiras. Fasc. I. O genero Sida. Revisao das especies brasileiras. 1 ª Parte. Chave das especies sul americanas e novidades brasileiras. Ministerio da Agricultura, Departamento Nacional de Producao Vegetal, Servico de Plantas Texteis, Rio de Janeiro, 56 pp." type="book" year="1936">Monteiro-Filho 1936</bibRefCitation>
, Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477C8DFA49224DFA0D" box="[1240,1303,1418,1444]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et. al.</emphasis>
2017) (
<tableCitation id="4A6403360B7616477D39FA4827CFFA61" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="2.[136,224,340,364]" captionTargetBox="[144,1440,425,1289]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="TABLE 1. Sections of Sida with species occurring in Rio Grande do Sul state, and their diagnostic features, according to Fryxell (1985) and Krapovickas (2003)." httpUri="http://table.plazi.org/id/539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" tableUuid="539966050B72164378DDFE962568FE39">Table 1</tableCitation>
), and is easily distinguished from related species by the presence of two long aristae in the mericarps, undulate (wavy) leaf margin, apex of the calyx and leaf margins dark-red or violaceous-purplish, calyx with trichomes 
<quantity id="C01E9B680B7616477DD4FA1027ECF9B8" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1–2 mm</quantity>
, and sulcate petioles (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B76164779E4FA3425D9F9B9" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[433,643,1526,1552]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref19319" refString="Krapovickas, A. (1969) Notas citotaxonomicas sobre Malvaceas. Bonplandia 3: 1 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 32 - 41441" type="journal article" year="1969">Krapovickas 1969</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477AC5FA34242FF9B9" author="Brandao, J. L. &amp; Baracho, G. S. &amp; De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V." box="[656,885,1526,1552]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="205 - 227" refId="ref18144" refString="Brandao, J. L., Baracho, G. S., De Sales, M. F. &amp; Filho, M. P. V. (2017) Synopsis of Sida (Malvaceae, Malvoideae, Malveae) in the state of Pernambuco, Brazil. Phytotaxa 307 (3): 205 - 227. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 307.3.5" type="journal article" year="2017">
Brandão 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477AA2FA35246AF9B9" box="[759,816,1526,1552]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2017
</bibRefCitation>
). Another diagnostic feature of this species are its relatively large, 16 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477931F9D9262DF99D" box="[356,375,1563,1588]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">×</emphasis>
<quantity id="C01E9B680B761647792AF9D8268BF99C" box="[383,465,1562,1589]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" unit="mm" value="10.0">10 mm</quantity>
, yellow-orange (sometimes salmon) petals, often with a red adaxial basal spot (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7616477D03F9D82791F9F1" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1920,1942]" captionTargetBox="[190,1398,187,1893]" captionTargetId="figure-25@4.[190,1398,187,1893]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–F. Sida anomala. A. Flower. B. Branch with flowers buds and leaves. C. Schizocarp. D. Branch leaves and stipules. E. Adaxial surface of leaf. F. Abaxial surface of leaf. G–L. Sida cerradoensis. G. Flower. H. Schizocarps and flower. I. Adaxial surface of leaf. J. Abaxial surface of leaf. K. Sulcate petiole. L. Schizocarp. M–Q. Sida confusa. M. Abaxial surface of leaf. N. Adaxial surface of leaf. O. Flower. P. Branch with schizocarp and leaves. Q. Peduncle and immature schizocarp. Photographs by Martin Grings and Marcio Verdi (O)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415489" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415489/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Figures 1G–L</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7616477882F9FC2653F9F1" box="[215,265,1598,1624]" captionStart="FIGURE 14" captionStartId="26.[136,229,1957,1979]" captionTargetBox="[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetId="figure-54@26.[196,1391,245,1933]" captionTargetPageId="26" captionText="FIGURE 14. Mericarps. A. Sida anomala. B. Sida confusa. C. Sida farroupilhensis. D. Sida glaziovii. E. Sida cerradoensis. F. Sida cordifolia. G. Sida dubia. H. Sida linifolia. I. Sida lonchitis. J. Sida nemorensis. K. Sida paradoxa. L. Sida planicaulis. M. Sida potentilloides.N. Sida reitzii. O. Sida regnellii. P. Sida rhombifolia.Q. Sida riedelii. R. Sida rubifolia.S. Sida spinosa.T. Sida tuberculata. U. Sida urens. V. Sida viarum. Photographs by Martin Grings." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415519" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415519/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">14E</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
