<subSubSection id="4FFC65060B76164778E8F9A026ADF8D1" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="0759368D0B76164778E8F9A026ADF8D1" blockId="6.[136,1452,1022,2057]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B76164778E8F9A025B4F9D5" bold="true" box="[189,750,1634,1660]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Distribution, habitat and conservation status:</emphasis>
—This species is known from 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477C0EF9A023EAF9D5" box="[1115,1200,1634,1660]" name="Bolivia" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Bolivia</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477C95F9A12272F9D4" box="[1216,1320,1635,1661]" name="Paraguay" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
and 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477D32F9A022F1F9D5" box="[1383,1451,1634,1660]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Brazil</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B76164778C5F944266CF909" author="Hassler, E." box="[144,310,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="34 - 47" refId="ref19077" refString="Hassler, E. (1910 a) Ex herbario hassleriano: novitates paraguariensis. IV. Repertorium Specierum Novarum Regni Vegetabilis 8: 34 - 47." type="journal article" year="1910">
Hassler 1910 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B761647797CF944266CF909" author="Krapovickas, A." box="[297,310,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 16" refId="ref19319" refString="Krapovickas, A. (1969) Notas citotaxonomicas sobre Malvaceas. Bonplandia 3: 1 - 16. https: // doi. org / 10.30972 / bon. 32 - 41441" type="journal article" year="1969">a</bibRefCitation>
</bibRefCitation>
, Krapovickas 1969, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477A71F9442452F909" author="Zuloaga, F. O. &amp; Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J." box="[548,776,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="1 - 3348" refId="ref20813" refString="Zuloaga, F. O., Morrone, O. &amp; Belgrano M. J. (2008) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares del Cono Sur (Argentina, sur de Brasil, Chile, Paraguay y Uruguay). Monographs in Systematic Botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden 107: 1 - 3348." type="journal article" year="2008">
Zuloaga 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477ADCF945259EF909" box="[649,708,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2008
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477B41F9442359F909" author="Alverson, W. S. &amp; Michel, L. R. C. de &amp; Dorr, L. J. &amp; Fryxell, P. A. &amp; Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I." box="[788,1027,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" pagination="786 - 819" refId="ref17710" refString="Alverson, W. S., Michel, L. R. C. de, Dorr, L. J., Fryxell, P. A., Krapovickas, A. &amp; Meneses, Q. R. I. (2014) Malvaceae. In: Jorgensen, P. M., Nee, M. H. &amp; Beck, S. G. (Eds.) Catalogo de las plantas vasculares de Bolivia, Monographs in systematic botany from the Missouri Botanical Garden. Missouri Botanical Garden Press., St. Louis, pp. 786 - 819." type="book chapter" year="2014">
Alverson 
<emphasis id="3592EA9F0B7616477BD1F94524E5F909" box="[900,959,1670,1696]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">et al.</emphasis>
2014
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477C44F94423FEF909" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1041,1188,1670,1696]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B7616477C8FF944227BF909" box="[1242,1313,1670,1696]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Brazil</collectingCountry>
, the species occurs in North, Northeast, Central-West, Southeast and South regions, but not in all states (
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B7616477CD0F968224DF96D" author="Bovini, M. G." box="[1157,1303,1706,1732]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref18092" refString="Bovini, M. G. (2020) Sida in Lista de Especies da Flora do Brasil. Jardim Botanico do Rio de Janeiro. Available from: http: // floradobrasil. jbrj. gov. br / jabot / floradobrasil / FB 9206 (accessed 7 July 2020)" type="url" year="2020">Bovini 2020</bibRefCitation>
). In Southern 
<collectingCountry id="7FF1761D0B76164778DDF90C2796F941" box="[136,204,1742,1768]" name="Brazil" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Brazil</collectingCountry>
occurs in 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7616477910F90C26CEF941" box="[325,404,1742,1768]" country="Brazil" name="Parana" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Paraná</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B76164779F4F90C251DF941" box="[417,583,1742,1768]" country="Brazil" name="Santa Catarina" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Santa Catarina</collectingRegion>
(first record) and 
<collectingRegion id="C522F86F0B7616477B4CF90C24B5F941" box="[793,1007,1742,1768]" country="Brazil" name="Rio Grande do Sul" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Rio Grande do Sul</collectingRegion>
(first record) states, found only in two localities in the latter, in Coastal grassland (
<figureCitation id="9FDD2A080B7616477A25F9302588F8A5" box="[624,722,1778,1804]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1971,1993]" captionTargetBox="[262,1350,253,1898]" captionTargetId="figure-17@5.[199,1389,190,1947]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 2. Distribution map of Sida anomala, S. cerradoensis, S. confusa, S. cordifolia, S. dubia, S. farroupilhensis and S. lonchitis in Rio Grande do Sul state, Brazil." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6415491" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6415491/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="111">Figure 2</figureCitation>
), in ruderal environments and anthropized grasslands. According to 
<bibRefCitation id="63774B7C0B76164778F3F8D42667F899" author="IUCN &amp; Cambridge, UK" box="[166,317,1814,1840]" pageId="6" pageNumber="111" refId="ref19221" refString="IUCN (2017) Guidelines for using the IUCN red list categories and criteria. Version 13. Gland, Switzerland and Cambridge, UK: Prepared by the Standards and Petitions Subcommitttee. Available from: http: // www. iucnredlist. org / documents / RedListGuidelines. pdf (accessed 3 November 2019)" type="url" year="2017">IUCN (2017)</bibRefCitation>
criteria, the species is here considered Least Concern (LC) with an EOO of 4,253,166.732 Km² and an AOO about 1,200 Km² and because it is a species that also occupies ruderal environments. Furthermore, it does not meet the criterion B(b) and B(c).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
